review_blob: Clear yellow with white head. Aroma fruity hops, caramel sweetness. Taste a nice grapefruit bitterness, grassy, fruity and light bodied. Refreshing. Nice one!
Pitch black with brown head. Aroma is rich roasted malts, coffee and some smoke, ashy rich. Taste bitter, chocolate, coffee, some sweetness. Alcohol aftertaste. Nice beer!

Bottle. Clear orange with white head. Aroma malty and bitter. Taste , this beer tastes really weird, bitter ashes and pepper, liquorice and burnt malts, salt? Hop character is weird and aftertaste is horrible. Not nice!

Bottle. Black with foamy light brown head. Aroma: Rich coffee and some roasted notes mixed with a nice hoppy character. Citrusy and piney. Taste bitter coffee and a real nice hoppy bitterness with grapefruit and pine. Alcohol is well hidden. A cool and bold brew! Cheers!
beer_name: To l Black Malts & Body Salts Black Coffee IIPA

review_blob: Clear orange with white head. Aroma nice fruity hops. Taste nice grapefruit bitterness and a light watery body. Refreshing and drinkable. Cheers!
From can. Hoppy somewhat malty a bit stale? Taste is a nice balance of fruity hops and caramel sweetness. Cheers!
Tap at Omnipollos Hatt. Hazy yellow beer with a super fruity and citrusy aroma. Taste is tropical fruits and bitter. Nice hop character in this one!
Bottle. Nice IPA , pretty malty. From backlog so dont remember taste notes that well.
I liked this saison! Nice flavour from the lemon and passion fruit while retaining a nice saison feel! Cheers!
The nice belgian blonde Duvel is there in the base. Quite interesting to add a more hops . I prefer the regular Duvel i think...
Bottle. OK IPA but nothing too special. Dark brown with sweet malt character. Refreshing!

From cellar. Should be coming up on four years now. Had it when it was released and remember it being pretty bad...now: pours a clear dark brown liquid with no head. Aroma: sweet caramelly malts, dark fruits, some coffee, smells nice. Taste: sweet caramel, booze, roasted coffee and malts. Quite smooth and thick sugary oily beer. Quite nice and better now than when released.
UPDATED: DEC 16, 2015
Tap at omnipollos hatt in Stockholm. I nice slightly sour spicy lemony saison. Refreshing and some Brett. Cheers.
Clear deep brown red with small foam. Aroma: cherry, candy cherry like the Haribo :P. Little artificial. Taste: nice aour taste with candy like cherry. Tastes like candy. Quite nice :)
Slightly hazy light orange yellow with white head. Aroma: sweet orange, tropical fruits. Bready malts. Taste: bitter grapefruit at the end. Some metallic taste. Bready. Something is of...

Bottle from cellar bought some 4years ago. Pours a dark brown black liquid with nice compact brown foam. Aroma is nice smooth chocolate, roasted, bourbon small vanilla some oak. Oats. Taste is smooth with bourbon and chocolate, roasted malts, some raisins and dark fruits. Nice and balanced , had this fresh also but cant remember the tasting notes from then. I like this one! Cheers!
Hazy yellow with white head. Nice fresh start aroma. Taste is little sour with refreshing citrus and little spice. Nice refreshing brew!

Nice copper clear with off white head. Aroma: nice fresh fruity hops and some caramel notes. Taste is nice level of bitterness and grapefruit. Some pine cone and toasty caramel. Nice and balanced IPA :) I like founders.
Can. Light yellow hazy with white fluffy head. Aroma is nice grassy hops, some citrusy perfume and hay. Nice! Taste: grassy and fresh hops, some tart citrus and watery. Nice and refreshing. Cheers!
Backlog. Drank this is Myanmar. Cant exactly remember but nothing that stands out. Cheers
Had this in a hotel room in Bagan. I am sorry to say this is the most horrible beer Ive had in a while...skynku, off tastes and alcohol. Uek

Backlog. Had this beer plenty in Myanmar. On a hot day a cold bottle of this looking out over the temples of Bagan or riding a boat in the Bengal bay this beer does the trick. Nothing special juat a pale lager.
Bottle from 7eleven in Tokyo. Not too impressive but fun to share with family in hotel room.
beer_name: Kirin Grand Kirin Galaxy Hop Session IPA

review_blob: Bottle at a restaurant. Clear brown Amber color. Aroma of malts, bread some slight bitter roasted toast. Taste, nice malty taste with some low bitterness at the end. Quite nice!

2011 bottle from own cellar. Deep clear red brown color. Beautiful. Fizzy head that disappeared quickly. Aroma is rich berries, raspberry, lingonberry, caramel, sweet plums. Nice sweet and complex. Taste: berries, candy, caramel, malty, thick mouthfeel with some alcohol there. Very nice!

2012 bottle from cellar. Black thick liquid. Aroma is very rich full of sweet dark fruits, coffee , complex amazing and chocolate. Dont k ow quite to describe it. Taste is sweet with nice raisin chocolate going on and complex flavours. amazing beer for beer day :). One of the better stouts Ive tasted and def. Best in a loooong time :).
beer_name: Three Floyds Dark Lord Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: 2011 bottle from own cellar. Pours a nice black thick liquid with brown head. Aroma is rich ofmliqourice, chocolate, dark fruits and roasted notes. Slightly sour with lemon and ashy notes. Liquorice and chocolate. Nah, a bit too aour for me but still a solid stout with rich mouthfeel. Cheers!
beer_name: Stone Imperial Russian Stout - Belgo Anise

review_blob: So, Chang, enjoyed this 60baht beer in the chaos of Khao san road after quite an adventure heading into Bangkok! Nice and refreshing but drink it quickly before it gets warmed by the 30+ temp. Cheers!
Bottle at pub in Kunming. Actually pretty good with some caramel malts and small roasted flavor going on. Refreshing aswell.
First beer from Laos. Started early win China ;) pretty good and refreshing lager. Works :)

beer_brewer_name: Guangdong Blue Ribbon Group - Beijing Lanbao Brewery (Naale)
review_blob: Can drank in hotel Im Hotan ,Xinjiang. Nice chocolate flavor with a smooth body. Quite good actually.
Slightly better than the Gold version but still pretty bad...less alcohol taste though. Had some bottles of this in Samarkand. Cheers!
Glass bottle 0.5l had in Samarkand. This is not a good beer. Even chilled there is def something of...so far Uzbekistan has not impressed me on the beer side...

I made it! Turkmenistan! Can drank at hotel room in Ashgabat. And I have to tell you, after 4 weeks of no beer in Iran this cold can tasted pretty darn good with some Russian music video on TV ;). The beer in itself is watery and a light light brew with nothing interesting going on. Refreshing though :)

Iran! Had a lot of different beers in Iran i.e. non alcoholic malt beverages. If you think of them as sodas with malt taste you wont be disappointed. Of all the flavors I tried in liked the peach one best! Perfect with a falafel sandwich. Taste is generally a thin malt body with fruit flavor added. Apparently it is popular for Iranians to buy the non alcohol malt version and add baking yeast to make their own brew :). Istak and Heyday are available almost everywhere. I tried : lemon, peach, melon, pomegranate, malt and grape. Melon was weiiiird. :)

Iran! Had a lot of different beers in Iran i.e. non alcoholic malt beverages. If you think of them as sodas with malt taste you wont be disappointed. Of all the flavors I tried in liked the peach one best! Perfect with a falafel sandwich. Taste is generally a thin malt body with fruit flavor added. Apparently it is popular for Iranians to buy the non alcohol malt version and add baking yeast to make their own brew :). Istak and Heyday are available almost everywhere. I tried : lemon, peach, melon, pomegranate, malt and grape. Melon was weiiiird. :)
Had on a rooftop bar in Istanbul. Refreshing when cold. Otherwise a pretty mediocre beer...
Two growlers shared with a friend in Freiburg. Really easy drinking brew and very refreshing. Cheers!
Several bottles of this when in Freiburg. Good brew and really refreshing. Good session beer!
Several bottles of this when in Freiburg. Solid refreshing beer with a good malty body. Enjoyed it!

Bottle at home. Deep Brown with off white head. Aroma: lots of barrel character with sweet dark fruits and sugar. Oaky and vanilla. Complex. Taste: plenty of barrel character, sweet, raisins, caramel, some booze! Really solid stuff. Cheers!

Bottle from cellar, first batch. Pours a thick pitch black liquid with a deep brown head that fizzes away pretty quick. Aroma is complex with lots of dark fruits, dark chocolate, booze, wood, little soy, smooth, sweet. Smells good! Taste: soooo rich, very complex profile. Sweet with a well hidden alcohol for its %. Hints of raisins, chocolate, soy, figs, vanilla. Really good stuff and has held up well since I had it some years ago.
beer_name: BrewDog / Ngne  / Mikkeller Black Tokyo* Horizon

review_blob: Bottle. Clear copper color with white head. Aroma: Very flowery and perfumy, fruity, some citrus in there, lemon, little bubblegum, smells interesting. Taste: sour at first with lemon and flowery notes and ends with a hoppy bitterness with grapefruit. Kind of a weird beer but ok.

Clear orange with white head. Aroma: Yes! White grape, citrus, tart, little hay and funkiness, overripe fruits, smells amazing! taste: Slight sourness with citrud character, lemon, hay, and a yeasty funkiness at the back, white grape,. Sour, fruity and well made saison!

Deep red with pink head. Aroma: cherries, slightly citrusy sour, but also a sweet component, little funk. Taste: cherries, nice amount of sourness, lemon, tart, overripe. Well made pretty clean kriek!
beer_name: New Belgium Lips of Faith - Transatlantique Kriek

review_blob: Light yellow with white head. Sparkling carbonation. Aroma: lemon, hay, slightly acidic, a little spice, fruity, wheat, def Brett. Taste: slightly acidic, funky Brett notes and a small grassy hopiness. Wheat and banana. Really refreshing and well made!

Bottle. Light yellow, slightly hazy. White fluffy head. Aroma: apples, a little funky, hay, small hop note, smells nice! Taste: small fruity bitterness, spicy, eatery, lively carbonation, good saison!

Cloudy light orange with big white head. Aroma: citrus, spicy,hay and Brett notes, smells really refreshing with classic saison notes. Taste: white grapes, citrus,fruits, dry and a nice bretty tone! Really nice one!
Tap. Clear golden with white head. Aroma of bisquity malts, bread and small hops. Taste is slightly bitter bready and slightly fruity, nothing too interesting but good session beer!
